150 grams Basmati Rice
2 unit(s) Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers
1 sachet(s) Cajun Spice Mix
1 unit(s) Avocado
30 grams Tomato Puree
10 grams Vegetable Stock Paste
1 sachet(s) Crispy Onions
75 grams Soured Cream
1 tbsp Honey
125 milliliter(s) Water

Boil a half-full kettle. Pour it into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the rice, 10-12 mins.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Heat a large frying pan on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Once hot, add the plant-based burgers and Cajun spice mix (add less if you'd prefer things milder) to the pan.
Use a spoon to mash the burgers into a mince-like texture as it cooks.
Cook until browned, 5-6 mins. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.
Meanwhile, cut the avocado into chunks.

Next, stir in the tomato puree, veg stock paste, honey and water (see pantry for both).
Simmer, 3-4 mins.

Share the rice between bowls and spoon over the veggie Cajun mince.
Top with the avocado.
Sprinkle over the crispy onions and drizzle with soured cream.
Enjoy!